[[Malta]] has a [[Mediterranean climate]] according to the [[Köppen climate classification]] (''Csa''),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/mt.html#Geo |title=The World Factbook |publisher=Cia.gov |date= |accessdate=2015-06-01}}</ref><ref>[http://www.doi.gov.mt/en/islands/location.asp] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090531132411/http://www.doi.gov.mt/en/islands/location.asp |date=31 May 2009 }}</ref> with very mild winters and warm to hot summers. Rain occurs mainly in winter, with summer being generally dry. According to the Troll-Paffen climate classification<ref>{{cite web|url=http://web.tiscali.it/linnets/Troll-Paffen.jpg |title=Tiscali Webspace |publisher=Web.tiscali.it |date= |accessdate=2015-06-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121004052732/http://web.tiscali.it/linnets/Troll-Paffen.jpg |archivedate=4 October 2012 |df=dmy }}</ref> and the Siegmund/Frankenberg climate classification,<ref>{{cite web|author=PH Heidelberg |url=http://www.ph-heidelberg.de/geographie/forschung-und-entwicklung/klimakarte-der-erde.html |title=Klimakarte der Erde: Pädagogische Hochschule Heidelberg |publisher=Ph-heidelberg.de |date= |accessdate=2015-06-01}}</ref> Malta lies within the subtropical zone, being at 35ºN latitude. == Temperature == The average yearly temperature is around {{convert|23|°C|°F|abbr=on}} during the day and {{convert|16|°C|°F|abbr=on}} at night (one of the warmest temperature averages in Europe). In the coldest month&nbsp;– January&nbsp;– the typical maximum temperature ranges from {{convert|12|to|18|C|F}} during the day and the minimum from {{convert|6|to|12|C|F}} at night. In the warmest month&nbsp;– August&nbsp;– the typical maximum temperature ranges from {{convert|28|to|34|C|F}} during the day and the minimum from {{convert|20|to|24|C|F}} at night. [[File:Malta International Airport3.jpg|thumb|right|A winter day in Malta: mild temperatures, sometimes cloudy or rainy, green vegetation.]]
Generally, April starts with temperatures from {{convert|17|-|22|C|F}} during the day and {{convert|10|-|14|C|F}} at night. November has temperatures from {{convert|17|-|23|C|F}} during the day and {{convert|11|-|18|C|F}} at night. However even in the remaining four months of the year (December, January, February and March) temperatures sometimes reach {{convert|20|°C|0|abbr=on}}. Amongst all capitals in the continent of Europe, Valletta—the capital of Malta—has the warmest winters, with average temperatures of around {{convert|16|°C|°F|abbr=on}} during the day and {{convert|10|°C|°F|abbr=on}} at night in the months of January and February. In March and December average temperatures are around {{convert|17|°C|°F|abbr=on}} during the day and {{convert|11|°C|°F|abbr=on}} at night.<ref name="Met Office">[http://www.maltairport.com/weather/page.asp?p=17148&l=1] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100906074233/http://www.maltairport.com/weather/page.asp?p=17148&l=1 |date=6 September 2010 }}</ref> The average number of days above {{convert|32|°C|°F|1}} is 15, most of which occur during July and August.<ref name = weatherbase.com /> In Malta large fluctuations in temperature are rare. Malta is one of only a handful of locations in Europe with a USDA [[hardiness zone]] of 11a.
== Daylight == Malta enjoys one of the most optimal arrangement of hours of daylight in Europe. Days in winter are not as short as in the northern part of the continent, the average hours of daylight in December, January and February is 10.3 hours<ref name = noaa >{{cite web | url = ftp://ftp.atdd.noaa.gov/pub/GCOS/WMO-Normals/RA-VI/ML/16597.TXT | title = Climate Data for Luqa | publisher = National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration | accessdate = 15 October 2012}}</ref> (for comparison: [[London]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/united-kingdom/london.php |title=London Climate and Weather Averages, UK |publisher=Weather2travel.com |date= |accessdate=2015-06-01}}</ref> or [[Moscow]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/russia-europe/moscow.php |title=Moscow Climate and Weather Averages, Russia (Europe) |publisher=Weather2travel.com |date= |accessdate=2015-06-01}}</ref> or [[Warsaw]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/poland/warsaw.php |title=Warsaw Climate and Weather Averages, Poland |publisher=Weather2travel.com |date= |accessdate=2015-06-01}}</ref> - about 8 hours). The shortest day of the year - 21 December - sunrise is around 7:00 and sunset is around 17:00. The longest day of the year - 21 June - sunrise is around 5:30 and sunset is around 20:30.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.weathercast.co.uk/world-weather/city-weather/poi/755X16641426/malta.html |title=City weather: The weather for Maltese Islands, Malta |publisher=Weathercast.co.uk |date=2007-01-30 |accessdate=2015-06-01}}</ref>
