== Sunshine == As one might expect from Malta's high daylight hours, Malta enjoys around 3,000 hours of sunshine per year (also one of the highest in Europe), from an average of above 5 hours of sunshine per day in December to an average of above 12 hours of sunshine per day in July.<ref name=MaltaWeather /><ref name="noaa"/> Thus, Malta enjoys about twice the amount of sunshine as cities in the northern half of Europe.{{citation needed|date=September 2016}} For comparison, [[London]] has 1,461 hours per year;<ref name=London_climate>{{cite web | url = http://www.metoffice.gov.uk/climate/uk/averages/19712000/sites/greenwich.html | title = Met Office: Climate averages 1971-2000 | publisher = [[Met Office]]|accessdate=2015-06-02 }}</ref> however, in winter Malta has much more sunshine. For comparison, London has 37 hours<ref name=London_climate /> while Malta has 161 hours of sunshine in December.<ref name=MaltaWeather />
