== Sea temperature == Average annual temperature of sea is {{convert|20|°C|°F|abbr=on}} (the highest annual sea temperature in Europe), from {{convert|15|-|16|C|F}} in the period from January to April to {{convert|26|°C|°F}} in August. In the 6 months from June to November, the average sea temperature exceeds {{convert|20|°C|°F|abbr=on}}. In May and December - the transition months - the average is around {{convert|18|°C|°F|abbr=on}}.
In the second half of April, which is the beginning of the summer/holiday season the average sea temperature is {{convert|17|°C|°F|abbr=on}}. The highest sea temperature is {{convert|27|°C|°F}} in the middle-3rd week of August. In late August and early September the temperature drops to {{convert|26|°C|°F}}, and in the second half of September it drops to {{convert|25|°C|°F}}. Around mid-October it drops to {{convert|24|°C|°F}}, and during the last week of October it drops to {{convert|23|°C|°F}}. By early November the temperature drops to {{convert|22|°C|°F}} (data of 2010).<ref name="Met Office"/><ref name="weather2travel">{{cite web|url=http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/malta/valletta.php |title=Valletta Climate Guide|publisher=Weather2travel.com |accessdate=5 June 2009}}</ref>
