{{Redirect|Hadrut}} {{Infobox settlement |official_name = Hadrut |native_name = Հադրութ |image_skyline = Hadrout003.JPG |image_caption = The centre of Hadrut |pushpin_map = Republic of Artsakh |pushpin_mapsize = 300 |subdivision_type = ''[[de facto]]'' Country |subdivision_name = {{flag|Artsakh}} |subdivision_type1 = ''de facto'' [[Administrative divisions of the Republic of Artsakh|Province]] |subdivision_name1 = [[Hadrut Region|Hadrut]] |subdivision_type2 = ''[[de jure]]'' Country |subdivision_name2 = {{flag|Azerbaijan}} |subdivision_type3 = ''de jure'' [[Administrative divisions of Azerbaijan|Rayon]] |subdivision_name3 = [[Khojavend Rayon|Khojavend]] |leader_title = |leader_name = |established_title = |established_date = |area_total_km2 = |area_footnotes = |population_as_of = 2015 |population_total = 4,100 <ref>http://stat-nkr.am/files/publications/2015/LXH_tverov_2015.pdf</ref> |population_density_km2 = auto |timezone = [[UTC]] |utc_offset = +4 |timezone_DST = |utc_offset_DST = |coordinates = {{coord|39|31|00|N|47|01|48|E|region:{{xb|NKR}}|display=inline,title}} |elevation_m = 720 |area_code = |website = }} '''Hadrut''' ({{lang-hy|Հադրութ}} {{lang-az|Hadrut}}) is de facto the administrative center of [[Hadrut Province (NKR)|Hadrut Province]], [[Republic of Artsakh|Artsakh]] and de jure a town in the [[Khojavend Rayon]] of [[Azerbaijan]]. The town has been de facto part of the [[Republic of Artsakh]] (formerly the ''Nagorno-Karabakh Republic'') since the end of the 1991-94 [[Nagorno-Karabakh War]]. According to NKR statistics, the town has a population of 4,100 as of 2015.<ref>http://stat-nkr.am/files/publications/2015/LXH_tverov_2015.pdf</ref>
==History== From 10 September 1939, Hadrut was the capital of the [[Hadrut District (NKAO)|Hadrut rayon]] within the [[Nagorno-Karabakh Autonomous Oblast]] of the [[Azerbaijan Soviet Socialist Republic]] until the abolishment of the Autonomous Oblast on 26 November 1991.<ref>Law of Azerbaijan Republic on Abolishment of Nagorno-Karabakh Autonomous Oblast of Azerbaijan Republic {{cite web |url=http://e-qanun.az/print.php?internal=view&target=1&docid=6783&doctype=0 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-08-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120424015234/http://e-qanun.az/print.php?internal=view&target=1&docid=6783&doctype=0 |archivedate=2012-04-24 |df= }}</ref>
During the [[Nagorno-Karabakh War]], the town was occupied by the [[Nagorno-Karabakh Defense Army]] on 2 October 1992.
The town is home to the "Mika-Hadrut Winery" for brandy, vodka and wine.
