{{Use Australian English|date=May 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox waterfall | name = Purling Brook Falls | photo = Purlingbrook Falls edit.jpg | photo_width = 250px | photo_caption = Purling Brook Falls, [[Springbrook, Queensland|Springbrook]] | map = Queensland | relief = yes | map_width = 250px | coordinates = {{coord|28|11|00|S|153|16|00|E|type:waterbody_region:AU-QLD_scale:50000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = <ref>{{Gazetteer of Australia|name=Purling Brook Falls (QLD)|feature=QLD27683}}</ref><ref name=dnrm>{{cite QPN|27683|Purling Brook Falls|accessdate=13 September 2015}}</ref> | location = [[South East Queensland|South East]] [[Queensland]], [[Australia]] | type = [[Waterfall#Types|Horsetail]] | elevation = | height = {{Convert|100|-|106|m}}<ref name=wow>{{cite web|url=http://www.world-of-waterfalls.com/australia-purling-brook-falls.html|title=Purling Brook Falls|work=World of Waterfalls|publisher=Johnny T. Cheng|date=16 May 2008|accessdate=30 May 2014}}</ref> | height_longest = | number_drops = 1 | width = | average_width = | watercourse = Purling Brook | average_flow = | world_rank = }} The '''Purling Brook Falls''' or sometimes incorrectly '''Purlingbrook Falls''', a [[Waterfall#Types|horsetail waterfall]] on the Purling Brook, is located in the [[UNESCO]] [[World Heritage Area|World Heritage]]{{endash}}listed [[Gondwana Rainforests]] in the [[South East Queensland|South East]] region of [[Queensland]], [[Australia]].
==Location and features== The Purling Brook Falls are situated within the central section of [[Springbrook National Park]] as part of the Shield Volcano Group, at [[Springbrook, Queensland|Springbrook]] which is part of the [[Gold Coast hinterland]], south-west of [[Surfers Paradise, Queensland|Surfers Paradise]].
After heavy rains the falling waters creates a spectacle that attracts large numbers of tourists. At these times the danger from falling rocks during [[landslide]]s can be hazardous so barricades are erected to prevent walking along tracks that pass the base of the falls.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goldcoast.com.au/article/2008/06/07/12187_gold-coast-feature.html|title=Walkers flirt with danger to visit falls|author= |accessdate=17 July 2009|date=7 June 2008|work=goldcoast.com.au |publisher=Gold Coast Publications }}</ref> ==See also== {{stack|{{Portal|Queensland|Environment}}}} * [[List of waterfalls of Australia#Queensland|List of waterfalls of Queensland]]
